==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoecake
<hw>Hoe"cake`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A cake of Indian
meal, water, and salt, baked before the fire or in the ashes; -- so
called because often cooked on a hoe.</def> <mark>[Southern
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

